# FormLens

A single-page survey analytics web app. Build custom surveys, import response data via CSV upload or paste, and get auto-generated visual reports with charts, percentage breakdowns, and word clouds — no backend required.

## Features

- **Survey Builder** — add multiple choice, checkbox, short answer, and rating questions
- **CSV Import** — drag and drop or paste CSV data exported from Google Forms, Typeform, or any survey tool
- **Auto-generated Reports** — charts and breakdowns are built automatically based on detected column types
- **Word Cloud** — open-ended text responses are analyzed for word frequency and rendered as an interactive word cloud
- **Print to PDF** — clean print stylesheet included for exporting reports

## Tech Stack

HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Chart.js

## Getting Started

No installation needed. Just open `index.html` in a browser.

```
git clone https://github.com/your-username/formlens.git
cd formlens
open index.html
```

## Usage

1. **Build** — add your survey questions in the Build tab
2. **Collect** — upload a CSV file or paste your data directly
3. **Analyze** — view the auto-generated report with charts and insights

Don't have a CSV file handy? Hit **Load sample dataset** to see the app in action.

## File Structure

```
formlens/
├── index.html    — markup and layout
├── styles.css    — all styling
└── app.js        — survey builder, CSV parsing, chart rendering
```